The study conducted by researchers at the University of Pennsylvania School of Medicine revealed that chronic sleep deprivation can stress the heart and increase the risk of cardiovascular disease and death.
Shift workers, who get less sleep due to disrupted circadian rhythms, are at higher risk.
Early risers may also face heart problems, as shown in a study in Kyoto.
Athletes, like college basketball players, perform better with adequate sleep.
Sleep deprivation affects memory consolidation and appetite regulation.
Lack of sleep can lead to weight gain and obesity, as well as hypertension.
Sleep hygiene education is crucial in preventing health issues.
